article.description: Gordon Hayward scored 25 points Saturday to lead Butler to an 84-55 victory over Illinois-Chicago.
article.headline: Hayward's 17 first-half points help Butler put away UIC early
article.linkText: Hayward-led Butler makes quick work of UIC
article.story: CHICAGO -- Gordon Hayward scored 25 points Saturday to lead Butler (No. 20 ESPN/USA Today) to an 84-55 victory over Illinois-Chicago. Hayward was 10-for-16 from the field and led the Bulldogs (16-4, 9-0 Horizon) with eight rebounds. Butler shot 56 percent from the field in the game and 13 players scored for the Bulldogs. Hayward scored 17 in the first half when Butler built a 37-26 lead. The Bulldogs extended the lead to 32 points with a minute to play. Butler scored 23 points off 13 UIC turnovers. Jeremy Buttell had 13 points and nine rebounds for the Flames (5-14, 1-8). Zavion Neely also had 13 points for Illinois-Chicago, which made 38 percent of its outside shots.
